A man was arrested on Friday on the N3 near Camperdown in KwaZulu-Natal for possession of a stolen car. According to Magma Security and investigation's Shaheen Sulieman, the car was reported stolen in Alberton, Gauteng. "We received information that the car was driving towards Durban and was caught near Camperdown," said Suliman. He said Camperdown police, SAPS flying squad and SSS security were all involved in the arrest. He said the driver was alone in the car with an unlicensed 9mm firearm. A case of possession of stolen property and unlicensed firearm is under investigation. KwaZulu-Natal police are yet to comment on the matter.